            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25, WILTON PLACE, S.W. ¶ London ¶ Oct 2 1868 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ Having now returned to town for the winter I have resumed printing. Three more sheets are in type but I have not the clean copies in tim...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">68.10.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M4, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, Times; ">25, WILTON PLACE, S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">London</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Oct 2 1868</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Having now returned to town for the winter I have resumed printing. Three more sheets are in type but I have not the clean copies in time for this mail and must defer them till the next. They contain <name key="Gentianeae">Gentianeae</name>
               <name key="Boragineae">Boragineae</name> &amp; the commencement of <name key="Convolvulaceae">Convolvulaceae</name>.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Bentham (1863-78), vol. 4, pp. 369-416. </p>
               </note> The remainder of that family and <name key="Solaneae">Solaneae</name> are at the printers and I am now at <name key="Scrophularineae">Scrophularineae</name>. I hope to get <name key="Utricularineae">Utricularineae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>Called Lentibularieae in Bentham (1863-78), vol. 4, pp. 523-33.</p>
               </note> and small Personate orders into this volume but <name key="Acanthaceae">Acanthaceae</name>
               <name key="Verbenaceae">Verbenaceae</name> and <name key="Labiatae">Labiatae</name> must stand over for the 5th<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the end, <name key="Acanthaceae">Acanthaceae</name> appeared in the 4th volume.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> In that volume after the above and small allied orders I shall take the Curvembryous orders (<name key="Nyctagineae">Nyctagineae</name>
               <name key="Phytolaccaceae">Phytolaccaceae</name>
               <name key="amaranthaceae">amaranthaceae</name>
               <name key="Chenopodiaceae">Chenopodiaceae</name> &amp; <name key="Polygoneae">Polygoneae</name>) then the <name key="Laurineae">Laurineae</name>
               <name key="Proteaceae">Proteaceae</name>
               <name key="Thymeleae">Thymeleae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <name key="Thymeleae">Thymeleae</name> were held over until the 6th volume.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> etc which I suppose will fill up the 5th vol. leaving the <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name>
               <name key="Urticeae">Urticeae</name> and other Orders of reduced structure for the 6th</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I found on my arrrival in town your <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name> which had come by the Essex but you will see by the above that it will be long before I shall come to them. This however is not of much consequence as they have been so recently worked up by J Mueller Baillon and yourself.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have received your letters of June and July for which many thanks — I see nothing requiring <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The page is torn at this point, and the following text is inserted from a fragment found elsewhere in the file.</p>
               </note>special answer but to thank you for all your good wishes and I get so tired of writing that I have not patience to enter into long correspondence.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As soon as this volume is printed I shall be obliged to proceed slowly as I have two or three other things that I must get on with — I shall however keep on steady work as long as I am able</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yours sincerely</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The box per Lincolnshire just received</p>
